  "texts": [
    "Denote the projection to the base circle by π: I → ∂.",
    "More concretely, for q = i a i z k i as above, a point on the circle ⟨q⟩ is given by a pair (θ, [q]), where θ ∈ ∂ is a point and [q] is the germ on a small sector around the direction θ of a holomorphic function q = i a i z k i, given by a choice of determination of z 1/r.",
    "We denote by π q: ⟨q⟩ → ∂ the corresponding covering (the restriction of π to ⟨q⟩).",
    "It is given by (θ, [q]) → θ.",
    "The integer r =: ram(q) is the ramification order of the circle ⟨q⟩."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}